f=Cybersecurity/cortex/operational/commands/cortex-commands.md · h1:cortex — Command Triggers=\| Trigger phrases \| Skill \| Shortcut \| · h1:cortex — Command Triggers=\|---\|---\|---\| · h1:cortex — Command Triggers=\| "detection rule," "alert triage," "SIEM," "false positive," "tune rule" \| detection-engineering \| /cortex-detection \| · h1:cortex — Command Triggers=\| "monitoring," "alert review," "severity," "triage queue," "runbook" \| security-monitoring \| /cortex-monitor \| · h1:cortex — Command Triggers=\| "incident," "breach," "IR," "forensics," "containment," "ransomware" \| security-incident-response \| /cortex-ir \| · h1:cortex — Command Triggers=\| "threat hunt," "hunt," "proactive," "hypothesis," "looking for" \| threat-hunting \| /cortex-hunt \| · h2:Precedence=**SEV1/SEV2 alerts** security-incident-response (immediate). Monitoring triage skipped confirmed critical incidents. **SEV3/SEV4 alerts** security-monitoring triage possible detection-engineering rule tuning. **Hunt findings** malicious security-incident-response. Suspicious detection-engineering new rules. **All containment actions** operator executes. cortex recommends (the security-inversion). **All post-incident lessons** warden's risk register. SEV1/SEV2 produces register updates.